No fewer than three people have been feared dead as over 30 people have fainted while waiting for the campaign team of the Peoples Democratic People (PDP) presidential candidate, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar at Sani Abacha Stadium, Kano on Sunday. Uncomfirmed reports have it that the alleged  death of the three people was as a result of a bloody clash  between rival groups of the PDP outside the stadium. The Nation reports that unprecedented crowd gathered at the venue waiting for the arrival of Atiku and his team for several hours. Those who fainted was as a result of suffocation inside the stadium,at the stadium was filled to the brim. As at the time of filling this report (4:30 P.M), Atiku and his team were yet to arrive the stadium.  Details later…